'''Vim''' ('''V'''i '''im'''proved) est un éditeur de texte basé sur l'éditeur de texte {{c|[[Wikipedia:Vi|vi]]}}. Il peut être utilisé à partir de la ligne de commande ou comme une application autonome avec une interface graphique.

== Installation ==

=== Options de la variable USE ===

{{USEflag|package=app-editors/vim}}

=== Vim en ligne de commande ===

Si le support pour le serveur X n'est pas nécessaire, installez {{Package|app-editors/vim}}:

{{Emerge|app-editors/vim}}

=== Vim en interface graphique ===

To install Vim with both the ncurses-based interface ({{Path|/usr/bin/vim}}) as well as the graphical interface (for the X Window System - {{Path|/usr/bin/gvim}}), install {{Package|app-editors/gvim}}:

{{Emerge|app-editors/gvim}}

There is also an experimental [[Qt]] interface called {{Package|app-editors/vim-qt}} which can also be installed.

=== Extensions ===

The category ''app-vim'' provides a lot of additional syntax definitions, plugins and other Vim related stuff.

Use {{c|emerge}} or {{c|eix}} to get an overview of available packages in the ''app-vim'' category:

{{Cmd|emerge --search "%@^app-vim"
|eix -cC app-vim}}

== Configuration ==

=== Fichiers ===

Vim can be configured on a per-user basis or through a system-wide configuration file:

* {{Path|/etc/vim/vimrc}} - The system wide (global) settings file.
* {{Path|~/.vimrc}} - The user-specific (local) configuration file. The tilde (~) means it is in the user's home directory.

